canonical:
  title: 謝花宴表
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 朝天述職欣瞻日月之光闢舘羅羞荐降雲霄之澤寵靈稠疊精爽震惶中謝 伏惟皇帝德尙包荒仁先字小俯憐偏國之賤介來賀聖朝之休辰粲洒賓閎重開燕豆盃傾玉醞留中山千日之香弁蔟瓊葩漏上苑九春之色淪肌以感沒齒難酬
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝花宴表
  author: 金克己
  language: lzh
  text: 朝天述職。欣瞻日月之光。闢舘羅羞。荐降雲霄之澤。寵靈稠疊。精爽震惶。中謝。 伏惟皇帝德尙包荒。仁先字小。俯憐偏國之賤介。來賀聖朝之休辰。粲洒賓閎。重開燕豆。盃傾玉醞。留中山千日之香。弁蔟瓊葩。漏上苑九春之色。淪肌以感。沒齒難酬。
korean:
  title: 사 화연 표
  author: 김극기
  language: kor
  text: |-
    천정(天庭)에 조회하여 조공을 받들며 해와 달의 빛을 기쁘게 우러러 뵈옴에 활짝 열린 빈관에 진수(珍羞)를 나열하여 운소(雲霄)의 은택을 푸짐히 내리시오니, 총영(寵榮)이 겹겹이 쌓여 정신이 아찔하였나이다. 중사(中謝)
    엎드려 생각하옵건대, 황제께옵서 덕은 오히려 거칠은 것을 포용하시고, 인(仁)은 먼저 작은 나라를 어루만지시어 변방 나라의 천한 사신이 성조(聖朝)의 아름다운 때를 하례함을 굽어 어여삐 여기셔서 빈관(賓館)을 찬란히 열고 연석을 거듭 차리오니, 잔에 넘치는 옥온(玉醞)은 중산(中山)  천일주(千日酒)의 향기를 머금었고, 탁상에 가득한 경파(瓊葩)는 상원(上苑) 구춘(九春)의 빛을 풍기어 뼛속에까지 스며드는 감격을 몸이 죽어도 보답하기 어렵도소이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0380_010_0320&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Expression of Gratitude for the Flower Banquet
  author: Kim Geuk-gi
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I ascend to the celestial court to offer tribute,
    Rejoicing to behold the radiance of sun and moon.
    The grand hall opens wide, displaying delicacies,
    As boundless grace descends from the clouds above.
    Wave upon wave of imperial favor overwhelms me,
    My spirit trembles in awe and gratitude.

    In humble reverence, I reflect:
    Your Majesty's virtue embraces even the rough and unpolished,
    Your benevolence reaches first to the small and distant.
    You have gazed with compassion upon this lowly envoy
    From a remote realm, honoring his presence at this glorious time.
    The guest halls shine resplendent, the banquet tables overflow,
    Cups brim with jade-like wine, bearing the fragrance of a thousand-day vintage,
    While flowers of jade adorn the feast, bearing the hues of eternal spring.
    This grace seeps into my very bones—
    A debt so profound that even death cannot repay it.
  footnotes:
    - The 'thousand-day vintage' (千日酒) refers to the famous wine from Zhongshan, celebrated in Chinese literary tradition for its exceptional quality and longevity.
    - The 'nine springs' (九春) is an allusion to eternal spring and perpetual renewal, suggesting the timelessness of imperial blessing.
    - This is a formal court document expressing gratitude, typical of the diplomatic poetry exchanged between tributary states and the imperial court.
